{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm going to tell you two things today:"},{"time":2000,"text":"One is what we have lost,"},{"time":4000,"text":"and two, a way to bring it back."},{"time":6000,"text":"And let me start with this."},{"time":8000,"text":"This is my baseline:"},{"time":10000,"text":"This is the Mediterranean coast"},{"time":13000,"text":"with no fish, bare rock"},{"time":16000,"text":"and lots of sea urchins that like to eat the algae."},{"time":20000,"text":"Something like this is what I first saw"},{"time":22000,"text":"when I jumped in the water for the first time"},{"time":25000,"text":"in the Mediterranean coast off Spain."},{"time":28000,"text":"Now, if an alien came to earth --"},{"time":31000,"text":"let's call him Joe --"},{"time":33000,"text":"what would Joe see?"},{"time":35000,"text":"If Joe jumped in a coral reef,"},{"time":38000,"text":"there are many things the alien could see."},{"time":41000,"text":"Very unlikely, Joe would jump"},{"time":43000,"text":"on a pristine coral reef,"},{"time":45000,"text":"a virgin coral reef with lots of coral, sharks, crocodiles,"},{"time":47000,"text":"manatees, groupers,"},{"time":49000,"text":"turtles, etc."},{"time":51000,"text":"So, probably, what Joe would see"},{"time":53000,"text":"would be in this part, in the greenish part of the picture."},{"time":57000,"text":"Here we have the extreme with dead corals,"},{"time":60000,"text":"microbial soup and jellyfish."},{"time":62000,"text":"And where the diver is,"},{"time":64000,"text":"this is probably where most of the reefs of the world are now,"},{"time":67000,"text":"with very few corals, algae overgrowing the corals,"},{"time":69000,"text":"lots of bacteria,"},{"time":71000,"text":"and where the large animals are gone."},{"time":74000,"text":"And this is what most marine scientists have seen too."},{"time":76000,"text":"This is their baseline. This is what they think is natural"},{"time":79000,"text":"because we started modern science"},{"time":81000,"text":"with scuba diving long after"},{"time":83000,"text":"we started degrading marine ecosystems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86000,"text":"So I'm going to get us all on a time machine,"},{"time":89000,"text":"and we're going to the left; we're going to go back to the past"},{"time":91000,"text":"to see what the ocean was like."},{"time":95000,"text":"And let's start with this time machine, the Line Islands,"},{"time":97000,"text":"where we have conducted a series"},{"time":99000,"text":"of National Geographic expeditions."},{"time":101000,"text":"This sea is an archipelago belonging to Kiribati"},{"time":103000,"text":"that spans across the equator"},{"time":105000,"text":"and it has several uninhabited,"},{"time":107000,"text":"unfished, pristine islands"},{"time":109000,"text":"and a few inhabited islands."},{"time":111000,"text":"So let's start with the first one: Christmas Island, over 5,000 people."},{"time":114000,"text":"Most of the reefs are dead,"},{"time":117000,"text":"most of the corals are dead -- overgrown by algae --"},{"time":120000,"text":"and most of the fish are smaller than"},{"time":122000,"text":"the pencils we use to count them."},{"time":125000,"text":"We did 250 hours of diving here"},{"time":127000,"text":"in 2005."},{"time":129000,"text":"We didn't see a single shark."},{"time":131000,"text":"This is the place that Captain Cook discovered in 1777"},{"time":134000,"text":"and he described a huge abundance of sharks"},{"time":137000,"text":"biting the rudders and the oars of their small boats"},{"time":140000,"text":"while they were going ashore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142000,"text":"Let's move the dial a little bit to the past."},{"time":144000,"text":"Fanning Island, 2,500 people."},{"time":146000,"text":"The corals are doing better here. Lots of small fish."},{"time":148000,"text":"This is what many divers would consider paradise."},{"time":150000,"text":"This is where you can see most"},{"time":152000,"text":"of the Florida Keys National Marine Sanctuary."},{"time":154000,"text":"And many people think this is really, really beautiful,"},{"time":157000,"text":"if this is your baseline."},{"time":159000,"text":"If we go back to a place"},{"time":161000,"text":"like Palmyra Atoll,"},{"time":163000,"text":"where I was with Jeremy Jackson a few years ago,"},{"time":166000,"text":"the corals are doing better and there are sharks."},{"time":169000,"text":"You can see sharks in every single dive."},{"time":171000,"text":"And this is something that is very unusual in today's coral reefs."},{"time":174000,"text":"But then, if we shift the dial"},{"time":176000,"text":"200, 500 years back,"},{"time":179000,"text":"then we get to the places where the corals"},{"time":181000,"text":"are absolutely healthy and gorgeous,"},{"time":183000,"text":"forming spectacular structures,"},{"time":185000,"text":"and where the predators"},{"time":187000,"text":"are the most conspicuous thing,"},{"time":190000,"text":"where you see between 25 and 50 sharks per dive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195000,"text":"What have we learned from these places?"},{"time":198000,"text":"This is what we thought was natural."},{"time":202000,"text":"This is what we call the biomass pyramid."},{"time":204000,"text":"If we get all of the fish of a coral reef together and weigh them,"},{"time":207000,"text":"this is what we would expect."},{"time":209000,"text":"Most of the biomass is low on the food chain, the herbivores,"},{"time":212000,"text":"the parrotfish, the surgeonfish that eat the algae."},{"time":215000,"text":"Then the plankton feeders, these little damselfish,"},{"time":218000,"text":"the little animals floating in the water."},{"time":221000,"text":"And then we have a lower biomass of carnivores,"},{"time":223000,"text":"and a lower biomass of top head,"},{"time":225000,"text":"or the sharks, the large snappers, the large groupers."},{"time":228000,"text":"But this is a consequence."},{"time":230000,"text":"This view of the world is a consequence"},{"time":232000,"text":"of having studied degraded reefs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"When we went to pristine reefs,"},{"time":236000,"text":"we realized that the natural world"},{"time":238000,"text":"was upside down;"},{"time":240000,"text":"this pyramid was inverted."},{"time":242000,"text":"The top head does account for most of the biomass,"},{"time":245000,"text":"in some places up to 85 percent,"},{"time":247000,"text":"like Kingman Reef, which is now protected."},{"time":250000,"text":"The good news is that, in addition to having more predators,"},{"time":252000,"text":"there's more of everything."},{"time":254000,"text":"The size of these boxes is bigger."},{"time":256000,"text":"We have more sharks, more biomass of snappers,"},{"time":259000,"text":"more biomass of herbivores, too,"},{"time":261000,"text":"like these parrot fish that are like marine goats."},{"time":264000,"text":"They clean the reef; everything that grows enough to be seen,"},{"time":267000,"text":"they eat, and they keep the reef clean"},{"time":270000,"text":"and allow the corals to replenish."},{"time":272000,"text":"Not only do these places --"},{"time":274000,"text":"these ancient, pristine places -- have lots of fish,"},{"time":276000,"text":"but they also have other important components"},{"time":278000,"text":"of the ecosystem like the giant clams;"},{"time":280000,"text":"pavements of giant clams in the lagoons,"},{"time":282000,"text":"up to 20, 25 per square meter."},{"time":284000,"text":"These have disappeared from every inhabited reef in the world,"},{"time":287000,"text":"and they filter the water;"},{"time":289000,"text":"they keep the water clean from"},{"time":291000,"text":"microbes and pathogens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293000,"text":"But still, now we have global warming."},{"time":296000,"text":"If we don't have fishing because these reefs are protected by law"},{"time":299000,"text":"or their remoteness, this is great."},{"time":301000,"text":"But the water gets warmer for too long"},{"time":303000,"text":"and the corals die."},{"time":305000,"text":"So how are these fish,"},{"time":307000,"text":"these predators going to help?"},{"time":309000,"text":"Well, what we have seen is that"},{"time":311000,"text":"in this particular area"},{"time":313000,"text":"during El Nino, year '97, '98,"},{"time":315000,"text":"the water was too warm for too long,"},{"time":317000,"text":"and many corals bleached"},{"time":319000,"text":"and many died."},{"time":321000,"text":"In Christmas, where the food web is really trimmed down,"},{"time":324000,"text":"where the large animals are gone,"},{"time":326000,"text":"the corals have not recovered."},{"time":328000,"text":"In Fanning Island, the corals are not recovered."},{"time":331000,"text":"But you see here"},{"time":334000,"text":"a big table coral that died and collapsed."},{"time":337000,"text":"And the fish have grazed the algae,"},{"time":339000,"text":"so the turf of algae is a little lower."},{"time":341000,"text":"Then you go to Palmyra Atoll"},{"time":343000,"text":"that has more biomass of herbivores,"},{"time":346000,"text":"and the dead corals are clean,"},{"time":349000,"text":"and the corals are coming back."},{"time":351000,"text":"And when you go to the pristine side,"},{"time":353000,"text":"did this ever bleach?"},{"time":356000,"text":"These places bleached too, but they recovered faster."},{"time":358000,"text":"The more intact, the more complete,"},{"time":360000,"text":"[and] the more complex your food web,"},{"time":362000,"text":"the higher the resilience, [and] the more likely"},{"time":365000,"text":"that the system is going to recover"},{"time":367000,"text":"from the short-term impacts of warming events."},{"time":370000,"text":"And that's good news, so we need to recover that structure."},{"time":373000,"text":"We need to make sure that all of the pieces of the ecosystem are there"},{"time":377000,"text":"so the ecosystem can adapt"},{"time":379000,"text":"to the effects of global warming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382000,"text":"So if we have to reset the baseline,"},{"time":385000,"text":"if we have to push the ecosystem back to the left,"},{"time":387000,"text":"how can we do it?"},{"time":389000,"text":"Well, there are several ways."},{"time":391000,"text":"One very clear way is the marine protected areas,"},{"time":393000,"text":"especially no-take reserves"},{"time":395000,"text":"that we set aside"},{"time":397000,"text":"to allow for the recovery for marine life."},{"time":399000,"text":"And let me go back to that image"},{"time":401000,"text":"of the Mediterranean."},{"time":404000,"text":"This was my baseline. This is what I saw when I was a kid."},{"time":407000,"text":"And at the same time I was watching"},{"time":409000,"text":"Jacques Cousteau's shows on TV,"},{"time":412000,"text":"with all this richness and abundance and diversity."},{"time":414000,"text":"And I thought that this richness"},{"time":416000,"text":"belonged to tropical seas,"},{"time":418000,"text":"and that the Mediterranean was a naturally poor sea."},{"time":420000,"text":"But, little did I know,"},{"time":422000,"text":"until I jumped for the first time in a marine reserve."},{"time":425000,"text":"And this is what I saw, lots of fish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428000,"text":"After a few years, between five and seven years,"},{"time":430000,"text":"fish come back, they eat the urchins,"},{"time":432000,"text":"and then the algae grow again."},{"time":434000,"text":"So you have this little algal forest,"},{"time":436000,"text":"and in the size of a laptop"},{"time":439000,"text":"you can find more than 100 species of algae,"},{"time":441000,"text":"mostly microscopic fit"},{"time":443000,"text":"hundreds of species of little animals"},{"time":446000,"text":"that then feed the fish,"},{"time":448000,"text":"so that the system recovers."},{"time":450000,"text":"And this particular place, the Medes Islands Marine Reserve,"},{"time":453000,"text":"is only 94 hectares,"},{"time":455000,"text":"and it brings 6 million euros to the local economy,"},{"time":458000,"text":"20 times more than fishing,"},{"time":460000,"text":"and it represents 88 percent"},{"time":462000,"text":"of all the tourist revenue."},{"time":464000,"text":"So these places not only help the ecosystem"},{"time":467000,"text":"but also help the people"},{"time":469000,"text":"who can benefit from the ecosystem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471000,"text":"So let me just give you a summary"},{"time":473000,"text":"of what no-take reserves do."},{"time":475000,"text":"These places, when we protect them,"},{"time":477000,"text":"if we compare them to unprotected areas nearby, this is what happens."},{"time":480000,"text":"The number of species increases 21 percent;"},{"time":482000,"text":"so if you have 1,000 species"},{"time":484000,"text":"you would expect 200 more in a marine reserve."},{"time":486000,"text":"This is very substantial."},{"time":488000,"text":"The size of organisms increases a third,"},{"time":491000,"text":"so your fish are now this big."},{"time":493000,"text":"The abundance, how many fish you have per square meter,"},{"time":496000,"text":"increases almost 170 percent."},{"time":499000,"text":"And the biomass -- this is the most spectacular change --"},{"time":502000,"text":"4.5 times greater biomass"},{"time":504000,"text":"on average, just after five to seven years."},{"time":506000,"text":"In some places up to 10 times"},{"time":508000,"text":"larger biomass inside the reserves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511000,"text":"So we have all these things"},{"time":514000,"text":"inside the reserve that grow, and what do they do?"},{"time":517000,"text":"They reproduce. That's population biology 101."},{"time":519000,"text":"If you don't kill the fish, they take a longer time to die,"},{"time":522000,"text":"they grow larger and they reproduce a lot."},{"time":525000,"text":"And same thing for invertebrates. This is the example."},{"time":527000,"text":"These are egg cases"},{"time":529000,"text":"laid by a snail off the coast of Chile,"},{"time":531000,"text":"and this is how many eggs they lay on the bottom."},{"time":534000,"text":"Outside the reserve,"},{"time":536000,"text":"you cannot even detect this."},{"time":538000,"text":"One point three million eggs per square meter"},{"time":541000,"text":"inside the marine reserve where these snails are very abundant."},{"time":545000,"text":"So these organisms reproduce,"},{"time":548000,"text":"the little larvae juveniles spill over,"},{"time":550000,"text":"they all spill over,"},{"time":552000,"text":"and then people can benefit from them outside too."},{"time":554000,"text":"This is in the Bahamas: Nassau grouper."},{"time":556000,"text":"Huge abundance of groupers inside the reserve,"},{"time":558000,"text":"and the closer you get to the reserve,"},{"time":560000,"text":"the more fish you have."},{"time":562000,"text":"So the fishermen are catching more."},{"time":564000,"text":"You can see where the limits of the reserve are"},{"time":566000,"text":"because you see the boats lined up."},{"time":568000,"text":"So there is spill over;"},{"time":570000,"text":"there are benefits beyond the boundaries of these reserves"},{"time":572000,"text":"that help people around them,"},{"time":574000,"text":"while at the same time"},{"time":576000,"text":"the reserve is protecting"},{"time":578000,"text":"the entire habitat. It is building resilience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582000,"text":"So what we have now --"},{"time":584000,"text":"or a world without reserves --"},{"time":586000,"text":"is like a debit account"},{"time":588000,"text":"where we withdraw all the time"},{"time":590000,"text":"and we never make any deposit."},{"time":592000,"text":"Reserves are like savings accounts."},{"time":594000,"text":"We have this principal that we don't touch;"},{"time":596000,"text":"that produces returns,"},{"time":598000,"text":"social, economic and ecological."},{"time":601000,"text":"And if we think about the increase of biomass inside the reserves,"},{"time":604000,"text":"this is like compound interest."},{"time":607000,"text":"Two examples, again,"},{"time":609000,"text":"of how these reserves can benefit people."},{"time":612000,"text":"This is how much fishermen get"},{"time":615000,"text":"everyday in Kenya, fishing"},{"time":617000,"text":"over a series of years,"},{"time":619000,"text":"in a place where"},{"time":621000,"text":"there is no protection; it's a free-for-all."},{"time":624000,"text":"Once the most degrading fishing gear,"},{"time":627000,"text":"seine nets, were removed,"},{"time":629000,"text":"the fishermen were catching more."},{"time":631000,"text":"If you fish less, you're actually catching more."},{"time":634000,"text":"But if we add the no-take reserve on top of that,"},{"time":636000,"text":"the fishermen are still making more money"},{"time":638000,"text":"by fishing less around an area that is protected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641000,"text":"Another example:"},{"time":643000,"text":"Nassau groupers in Belize in the Mesoamerican Reef."},{"time":646000,"text":"This is grouper sex,"},{"time":648000,"text":"and the groupers aggregate around the full moons"},{"time":650000,"text":"of December and January for a week."},{"time":653000,"text":"They used to aggregate up to the"},{"time":656000,"text":"tens of thousands, 30,000 groupers about this big"},{"time":658000,"text":"in one hectare, in one aggregation."},{"time":661000,"text":"Fishermen knew about these things; they caught them, and they depleted them."},{"time":664000,"text":"When I went there for the first time in 2000,"},{"time":667000,"text":"there were only 3,000 groupers left."},{"time":669000,"text":"And the fishermen were authorized to catch 30 percent"},{"time":672000,"text":"of the entire spawning population every year."},{"time":675000,"text":"So we did a simple analysis,"},{"time":677000,"text":"and it doesn't take rocket science"},{"time":679000,"text":"to figure out that, if you take 30 percent every year,"},{"time":681000,"text":"your fishery is going to collapse very quickly."},{"time":683000,"text":"And with the fishery, the entire reproductive ability"},{"time":685000,"text":"of the species goes extinct."},{"time":687000,"text":"It happened in many places around the Caribbean."},{"time":690000,"text":"And they would make 4,000 dollars per year,"},{"time":692000,"text":"total, for the entire fishery,"},{"time":694000,"text":"several fishing boats."},{"time":697000,"text":"Now, if you do an economic analysis"},{"time":699000,"text":"and project what would happen"},{"time":701000,"text":"if the fish were not cut,"},{"time":703000,"text":"if we brought just 20 divers"},{"time":705000,"text":"one month per year,"},{"time":707000,"text":"the revenue would be more than 20 times higher"},{"time":710000,"text":"and that would be sustainable over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":713000,"text":"So how much of this do we have?"},{"time":715000,"text":"If this is so good, if this is such a no-brainer, how much of this do we have?"},{"time":718000,"text":"And you already heard that"},{"time":720000,"text":"less than one percent of the ocean's protected."},{"time":722000,"text":"We're getting closer to one percent now,"},{"time":724000,"text":"thanks to the protections of the Chagos Archipelago,"},{"time":726000,"text":"and only a fraction of this is fully protected from fishing."},{"time":730000,"text":"Scientific studies recommend that at least 20 percent"},{"time":732000,"text":"of the ocean should be protected."},{"time":735000,"text":"The estimated range is between 20 and 50 percent"},{"time":737000,"text":"for a series of goals of biodiversity"},{"time":739000,"text":"and fishery enhancement and resilience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":742000,"text":"Now, is this possible? People would ask: How much would that cost?"},{"time":745000,"text":"Well, let's think about"},{"time":747000,"text":"how much we are paying now"},{"time":749000,"text":"to subsidize fishing:"},{"time":752000,"text":"35 billion dollars per year."},{"time":756000,"text":"Many of these subsidies go to destructive fishing practices."},{"time":759000,"text":"Well, there are a couple estimates"},{"time":761000,"text":"of how much it would cost to create"},{"time":763000,"text":"a network of protected areas"},{"time":765000,"text":"covering 20 percent of the ocean"},{"time":767000,"text":"that would be only a fraction"},{"time":769000,"text":"of what we are now paying;"},{"time":771000,"text":"the government hands out to a fishery"},{"time":773000,"text":"that is collapsing."},{"time":775000,"text":"People are losing their jobs because the fisheries are collapsing."},{"time":778000,"text":"A creation of a network of reserves"},{"time":780000,"text":"would provide direct employment for more than a million people"},{"time":782000,"text":"plus all the secondary jobs and all the secondary benefits."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785000,"text":"So how can we do that?"},{"time":787000,"text":"If it's so clear that these savings accounts"},{"time":790000,"text":"are good for the environment and for people,"},{"time":793000,"text":"why don't we have 20, 50 percent of the ocean?"},{"time":796000,"text":"And how can we reach that goal?"},{"time":799000,"text":"Well, there are two ways of getting there."},{"time":802000,"text":"The trivial solution is to create really large protected areas"},{"time":805000,"text":"like the Chagos Archipelago."},{"time":807000,"text":"The problem is that we can create these large reserves"},{"time":810000,"text":"only in places where there are no people, where there is no social conflict,"},{"time":813000,"text":"where the political cost is really low"},{"time":815000,"text":"and the economic cost is also low."},{"time":818000,"text":"And a few of us, a few organizations in this room and elsewhere"},{"time":821000,"text":"are working on this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823000,"text":"But what about the rest of the coast of the world,"},{"time":825000,"text":"where people live and make a living out of fishing?"},{"time":829000,"text":"Well, there are three main reasons why"},{"time":831000,"text":"we don't have tens of thousands of small reserves:"},{"time":834000,"text":"The first one is that people have no idea"},{"time":836000,"text":"what marine reserves do,"},{"time":839000,"text":"and fishermen tend to be really, really defensive"},{"time":842000,"text":"when it comes to regulating or closing"},{"time":844000,"text":"an area, even if it's small."},{"time":846000,"text":"Second, the governance is not right"},{"time":848000,"text":"because most coastal communities around the world"},{"time":850000,"text":"don't have the authority"},{"time":852000,"text":"to monitor the resources to create the reserve and enforce it."},{"time":855000,"text":"It's a top down hierarchical structure"},{"time":857000,"text":"where people wait for"},{"time":859000,"text":"government agents to come"},{"time":861000,"text":"and this is not effective. And the government doesn't have enough resources."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864000,"text":"Which takes us to the third reason,"},{"time":866000,"text":"why we don't have many more reserves,"},{"time":869000,"text":"is that the funding models have been wrong."},{"time":872000,"text":"NGOs and governments"},{"time":874000,"text":"spend a lot of time and energy and resources"},{"time":877000,"text":"in a few small areas, usually."},{"time":880000,"text":"So marine conservation and coastal protection"},{"time":882000,"text":"has become a sink for government or philanthropic money,"},{"time":885000,"text":"and this is not sustainable."},{"time":887000,"text":"So the solutions are just"},{"time":889000,"text":"fixing these three issues."},{"time":891000,"text":"First, we need to develop a global awareness campaign"},{"time":894000,"text":"to inspire local communities and governments"},{"time":897000,"text":"to create no-take reserves"},{"time":899000,"text":"that are better than what we have now."},{"time":901000,"text":"It's the savings accounts"},{"time":903000,"text":"versus the debit accounts with no deposits."},{"time":906000,"text":"Second, we need to redesign our governance"},{"time":908000,"text":"so conservation efforts can be decentralized,"},{"time":911000,"text":"so conservation efforts don't depend on"},{"time":914000,"text":"work from NGOs"},{"time":916000,"text":"or from government agencies"},{"time":918000,"text":"and can be created by the local communities,"},{"time":920000,"text":"like it happens in the Philippines and a few other places."},{"time":923000,"text":"And third, and very important,"},{"time":925000,"text":"we need to develop new business models."},{"time":928000,"text":"The philanthropy sink as the only way to create reserves"},{"time":931000,"text":"is not sustainable."},{"time":933000,"text":"We really need to develop models, business models,"},{"time":936000,"text":"where coastal conservation"},{"time":939000,"text":"is an investment,"},{"time":941000,"text":"because we already know"},{"time":943000,"text":"that these marine reserves provide"},{"time":945000,"text":"social, ecological and economic benefits."}]},{"cues":[{"time":948000,"text":"And I'd like to finish with one thought,"},{"time":951000,"text":"which is that no one"},{"time":953000,"text":"organization alone"},{"time":955000,"text":"is going to save the ocean."},{"time":957000,"text":"There has been a lot of competition in the past,"},{"time":960000,"text":"and we need to develop"},{"time":962000,"text":"a new model of partnership,"},{"time":964000,"text":"truly collaborative,"},{"time":966000,"text":"where we are looking for complementing,"},{"time":968000,"text":"not substituting."},{"time":970000,"text":"The stakes are just too high"},{"time":972000,"text":"to continue the way we are going."},{"time":974000,"text":"So let's do that. Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":976000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":984000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Thank you Enric."}]},{"cues":[{"time":986000,"text":"Enric Sala: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":989000,"text":"CA: That was a masterful job"},{"time":991000,"text":"of pulling things together."},{"time":993000,"text":"First of all, your pyramid, your inverted pyramid,"},{"time":996000,"text":"showing 85 percent biomass in the predators,"},{"time":998000,"text":"that seems impossible."},{"time":1000000,"text":"How could 85 percent"},{"time":1003000,"text":"survive on 15 percent?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1005000,"text":"ES: Well, imagine that you have two gears"},{"time":1008000,"text":"of a watch, a big one and a small one."},{"time":1010000,"text":"The big one is moving very slowly, and the small one is moving fast."},{"time":1013000,"text":"That's basically it."},{"time":1015000,"text":"The animals at the lower parts of the food chain,"},{"time":1018000,"text":"they reproduce very fast; they grow really fast; they produce millions of eggs."},{"time":1021000,"text":"Up there, you have sharks and large fish that live 25, 30 years."},{"time":1024000,"text":"They reproduce very slowly; they have a slow metabolism;"},{"time":1027000,"text":"and, basically, they just maintain their biomass."},{"time":1029000,"text":"So, basically, the production surplus of these guys down there"},{"time":1032000,"text":"is enough to maintain this biomass"},{"time":1034000,"text":"that is not moving."},{"time":1036000,"text":"They are like capacitors of the system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1039000,"text":"CA: That's very fascinating."},{"time":1041000,"text":"So, really, our picture of a food pyramid"},{"time":1043000,"text":"is just -- we have to change that completely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1045000,"text":"ES: At least in the seas."},{"time":1048000,"text":"What we found in coral reefs is that the inverted pyramid"},{"time":1050000,"text":"is the equivalent of the Serengeti,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"with five lions per wildebeest."},{"time":1054000,"text":"And on land, this cannot work."},{"time":1056000,"text":"But at least on coral reefs are systems"},{"time":1058000,"text":"where there is a bottom component with structure."},{"time":1060000,"text":"We think this is universal."},{"time":1062000,"text":"But we have started studying pristine reefs"},{"time":1065000,"text":"only very recently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1067000,"text":"CA: So the numbers you presented really are astonishing."},{"time":1070000,"text":"You're saying we're spending 35 billion dollars"},{"time":1072000,"text":"now on subsidies."},{"time":1074000,"text":"It would only cost 16 billion to set up"},{"time":1076000,"text":"20 percent of the ocean as"},{"time":1079000,"text":"marine protected areas"},{"time":1081000,"text":"that actually give new living choices"},{"time":1083000,"text":"to the fishermen as well."},{"time":1085000,"text":"If the world was a smarter place,"},{"time":1087000,"text":"we could solve this problem for negative 19 billion dollars."},{"time":1090000,"text":"We've got 19 billion to spend on health care or something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1092000,"text":"ES: And then we have the under-performance of fisheries"},{"time":1095000,"text":"that is 50 billion dollars."},{"time":1098000,"text":"So again, one of the big solutions is"},{"time":1100000,"text":"have the World Trade Organization shifting the subsidies"},{"time":1102000,"text":"to sustainable practices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1105000,"text":"CA: Okay, so there's a lot of examples that I'm hearing out there"},{"time":1107000,"text":"about ending this subsidies madness."},{"time":1109000,"text":"So thank you for those numbers."},{"time":1111000,"text":"The last one's a personal question."},{"time":1113000,"text":"A lot of the experience of people here"},{"time":1115000,"text":"who've been in the oceans for a long time"},{"time":1117000,"text":"has just been seeing this degradation, the places they saw that were beautiful"},{"time":1120000,"text":"getting worse, depressing."},{"time":1122000,"text":"Talk to me about the feeling that you must have experienced"},{"time":1124000,"text":"of going to these pristine areas"},{"time":1127000,"text":"and seeing things coming back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1130000,"text":"ES: It is a spiritual experience."},{"time":1133000,"text":"We go there to try to understand the ecosystems,"},{"time":1135000,"text":"to try to measure or count fish and sharks"},{"time":1138000,"text":"and see how these places are different from the places we know."},{"time":1141000,"text":"But the best feeling"},{"time":1144000,"text":"is this biophilia that E.O. Wilson talks about,"},{"time":1146000,"text":"where humans have this sense of awe and wonder"},{"time":1149000,"text":"in front of untamed nature, of raw nature."},{"time":1152000,"text":"And there, only there,"},{"time":1154000,"text":"you really feel that you are part of a larger thing"},{"time":1157000,"text":"or of a larger global ecosystem."},{"time":1160000,"text":"And if it were not for these places that show hope,"},{"time":1163000,"text":"I don't think I could continue doing this job."},{"time":1165000,"text":"It would be just too depressing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1167000,"text":"CA: Well, Enric, thank you so much for sharing"},{"time":1169000,"text":"some of that spiritual experience with us all. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1171000,"text":"ES: Thank you very much."}]}]}